question:
District category contains Business District, Silicon Valley, University Campus, and Financial District.
Supermarkets category contains Metro (Canada), and Grocery Outlet.
The number of each Silicon Valley 's Grocery Outlet equals 16 times the sum of each University Campus 's Grocery Outlet and each Business District 's Grocery Outlet.
The number of each University Campus 's Grocery Outlet equals 21.
The number of each Business District 's Grocery Outlet equals 4 more than each University Campus 's Grocery Outlet.
The number of each Silicon Valley 's Metro (Canada) equals each Financial District 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Financial District 's Metro (Canada) equals the difference of each University Campus 's Grocery Outlet and each University Campus 's Supermarkets.
The number of each University Campus 's Metro (Canada) equals 9.
How many Metro (Canada) does University Campus have?
solution: Define each University Campus 's Metro (Canada) as t; So t = 9.
